Roger Garrett (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Roger_Garrett_(actor) 0 Roger Lee Garrett (July 16, 1940 – May 23, 2000) was an American actor. He acted on stage, and played supporting roles in television series and films. He had a starring role in the West Coast production of Fortune and Men's Eyes (1969), and a starring role in the horror/thriller motion picture Night of the Cobra Woman (1972). Some of the big name performers that Garrett appeared opposite are Elizabeth Montgomery, Barbara Eden, Larry Hagman, Don Johnson, Jacqueline Bisset, Tuesday Weld, and Jack Nicholson.
